headline: 3 Reasons to Sell GPC and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the last six months, Genuine Parts’s shares have sunk to $116.96, producing a disappointing 12.6% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 8.8% gain. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
